# =============================================================================
# docker-syncd-vs (platform/vs/docker-syncd-vs + docker-syncd-trixie.mk template).
#
# Ground truth = the Make image package delta (target/IMG.gz minus the
# docker-config-engine-trixie base), which is IDENTICAL for docker-syncd-vs and
# docker-gbsyncd-vs (267 packages). 7 are SONiC-built (sonic_pkgs below); 257 are
# Debian apt (apt_layer below), registered in the shared @trixie pool
# (dockers/docker-base-trixie/base_trixie.MODULE.bazel).
#
# The remaining 3 (p4lang-bmv2 / p4lang-p4c / p4lang-pi) are intentionally NOT
# shipped: they are NOT Debian apt packages (absent from the trixie snapshot) and
# their only source is the non-hermetic @p4lang make-bridge (src/p4lang/BUILD.bazel
# uses local=True + no-sandbox to shell out to SONiC `make`), which the hermetic
# rules-of-migration forbid for image assembly. They are also NOT runtime deps:
# the libsai deb has an empty Depends field and libsai.so's DT_NEEDED is only
# libstdc++ / libgcc_s / libc (verified on the Make image). They are build-time
# baggage left in the runtime image (like the gcc/clang/llvm toolchain the
# Dockerfile also leaves installed). Documented as an accepted difference in the
# migration diff report.
#
# Dockerfile.j2 build stage:
#   ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
#   apt-get install -f -y libcap2-bin
#   dpkg -i libnl-3-dev libnl-route-3-dev              (SONiC-patched; DASH build)
#   apt-get install -f -y <long runtime + -dev list>   (left in the runtime image)
#   dpkg -i docker_<img>_debs  (SYNCD_VS closure: libsairedis/metadata/vs + libsai
#                               via INCLUDE_VS_DASH_SAI=y, pulling p4lang/boost/
#                               llvm/openmpi/ROCm/Qt5 apt closure through apt -f)
#   COPY start.sh -> /usr/bin ; supervisord.conf -> /etc/supervisor/conf.d ;
#        critical_processes -> /etc/supervisor
#   final stage: FROM $BASE + rsync_from_builder_stage() squashes the delta onto
#   the base; ENTRYPOINT ["/usr/local/bin/supervisord"].
#
# flatten() does NOT resolve deb Depends, so every apt closure member (all 260)
# is listed explicitly as @trixie//<pkg>:data. The bookworm sonic-bazel reference
# BUILD.bazel is NOT a usable template here: it targets bookworm and predates the
# INCLUDE_VS_DASH_SAI=y libsai/p4lang closure (it lists neither), and it COPYs a
# python supervisor-proc-exit-listener that this Dockerfile.j2 does not.
# =============================================================================
flatten(
    name = "apt_layer",
    deduplicate = True,
    tars = [
        "@trixie//autoconf:data",
